26/05/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Police in Mitrovica arrested six fellow officers and a civilian on Wednesday (May 25th) for suspected smuggling, abuse of office and taking bribes. 
All of them are ethnic Albanians. 
Kosovo Police spokesperson Baki Kelani said that the action was conducted by the Anti-corruption Taskforce Unit and Kosovo Tax Administration officials. 
Investigators say the suspects smuggled various goods from the north to the southern part of divided town. 
(Koha.Net, RTK, Klan Kosova, Kohavision - 25/05/11)
